Place the roasted red peppers, garlic, chilli flakes, tomato pur√©e, olive oil, oregano, Tabasco, salt and freshly ground black pepper into a mini blender and blend until almost smooth. Set aside.Cook the pasta according to the packet instructions and drain, leaving a little of the cooking liquid in the bottom of the pan. Add the roasted pepper sauce to the hot pasta and stir well.To serve, spoon into a serving bowl, scatter with grated pecorino and garnish with basil leaves.